menu "IMU Slave Configuration"

    config SLAVE_MASTER_MAC
        string "Master MAC address (XX:XX:XX:XX:XX:XX)"
        default "AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF"
        help
            Unicast target for ESP-NOW transmissions.
            Flash the master firmware first and read its MAC from the serial
            log ("Master MAC: XX:XX:XX:XX:XX:XX"), then enter it here.

    config SLAVE_I2C_SDA_PIN
        int "BNO055 I2C SDA GPIO"
        default 6
        range 0 21
        help
            GPIO number connected to BNO055 SDA.
            XIAO ESP32C3: GPIO6 is the dedicated SDA pin.

    config SLAVE_I2C_SCL_PIN
        int "BNO055 I2C SCL GPIO"
        default 7
        range 0 21
        help
            GPIO number connected to BNO055 SCL.
            XIAO ESP32C3: GPIO7 is the dedicated SCL pin.

    config SLAVE_BNO055_ADDR
        hex "BNO055 I2C address"
        default 0x28
        help
            0x28 when the ADDR pin is LOW (default Adafruit breakout).
            0x29 when the ADDR pin is pulled HIGH.

    config SLAVE_SAMPLE_RATE_HZ
        int "Sample rate (Hz)"
        default 50
        range 1 100
        help
            How often the BNO055 is read and a packet is sent to the master.
            The BNO055 NDOF fusion output refreshes at 100 Hz maximum; values
            above that will not yield additional unique samples.

    config SLAVE_ESPNOW_CHANNEL
        int "Wi-Fi channel for ESP-NOW"
        default 1
        range 1 13
        help
            MUST match the channel of the Wi-Fi AP the master is connected to.
            Check your router/AP admin panel for the 2.4 GHz channel in use
            and set the same value here.  A mismatch means ESP-NOW packets
            will not reach the master.

endmenu
